-- Iran to Invest $30 Billion in Oil Industry This Year, Shana Says
-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 2012-04-04T10:01:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/iran-to-invest-30-billion-in-oil-industry-this-year-shana-says.html
Iran  will invest at least $30
billion in its oil industry this year, much of it for projects
in the South Pars gas field, the oil ministry’s website  Shana 
reported, citing Oil Minister Rostam Qasemi, who didn’t give any
further details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladane Nasseri in Dubai at 
